metadata.description:
Just some encouragement to Believe in yourself.
Felt the need to speak this onto you.

lyrics.text:
I find that people question more than once
Where they’ll end up, happier than some
To most the bare minimum is good enough
Can’t hold that belief in me
Hanging still’ like empty vessel
With emotions at the peril
Can’t live in fear at the thought though
So I gotta believe in me
But if any truth’s weighing more than tons 
If you find your tongue
Don’t put any thoughts out there
That favor rain
We’re only here to swim
Lightly treading
Those deep waters yeah
Bon Voyage

metadata.name: Belief #1
metadata.title: Belief
